com.hp.hpl.jena.sparql.core

Interface DatasetGraph

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Closeable
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    GraphStore
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    DatasetGraphAltDefaultGraph, DatasetGraphBase, DatasetGraphBaseFind, DatasetGraphCaching, DatasetGraphCollection, DatasetGraphMaker, DatasetGraphMap, DatasetGraphMonitor, DatasetGraphOne, DatasetGraphQuad, DatasetGraphReadOnly, DatasetGraphSimpleMem, DatasetGraphTrackActive, DatasetGraphTriplesQuads, DatasetGraphViewGraphs, DatasetGraphWithLock, DatasetGraphWrapper, DynamicDatasets.DynamicDatasetGraph, GraphStoreBasic, GraphStoreNull, GraphStoreNullTransactional, GraphStoreWrapper

    public interface DatasetGraph
extends Closeable
    DatasetGraph: The graph representation of an RDF Dataset. See Dataset for the Model level of an RDF dataset.

    Whether a dataset contains a graph if there are no triples is not defined; see the specific implementation.

        Set the default graph. Set the active graph if it was null. This replaces the contents default graph, not merge data into it. Do not assume that the same object is returned by getDefaultGraph()

      • addGraph

        void addGraph(Node graphName,
            Graph graph)
        Add the given graph to the dataset. Replaces any existing data for the named graph; to add data, get the graph and add triples to it, or add quads to the dataset. Do not assume that the same Java object is returned by getGraph(com.hp.hpl.jena.graph.Node)
